title.narrative: Output 5.2: Staff and partners are provided guidance tools and resources for effective communication on child rights issues

description.narrative: Effective public advocacy on children’s rights, by UNICEF Kenya and partners, was increased through strategic communication campaigns and activities, including on COVID-19. This included new partnerships with the media and telecoms; knowledge products to support advocacy for children’s rights; high-profile launch events, interviews, and videos to improve media coverage of UNICEF’s work; engagement of young people, celebrities and other influencers; and creative use of social media and multi-media content for storytelling. As a result, the number of people reached by UNICEF substantially increased through traditional media (estimated at 36 million), social media (7.9 million) and mobile SMS (7.8 million). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/01/2022
